WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

1
00:00:01.766 --> 00:00:09.399
If you’re an enterprise device user, you’ll need to sign in to your Samsung business account before you can launch your Galaxy AI features.

2
00:00:09.833 --> 00:00:14.199
To sign in, go to the Settings app, then tap Galaxy AI.

3
00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:17.966
If you're using a fully managed device, tap Continue.

4
00:00:17.966 --> 00:00:22.766
On the following screen, enter your business account email, then tap Sign in.

5
00:00:23.566 --> 00:00:30.366
If you have a Corporate Owned, Personally Enabled devices, first select your work profile, then tap Continue.

6
00:00:30.366 --> 00:00:35.299
On the following screen, enter your business account email, then tap Sign in.

7
00:00:36.366 --> 00:00:42.299
After signing in, you’ll see the list of available Galaxy AI features assigned to you by your admin. 

8
00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:46.663
If an AI feature is blocked by your admin, you’ll see the feature on screen, 

9
00:00:46.664 --> 00:00:50.368
but you won’t be able to use the feature or configure any settings.

10
00:00:50.368 --> 00:00:53.832
Note that you may be required to download some AI features,

11
00:00:53.833 --> 00:00:57.133
even if your admin granted you permission to use them.

12
00:00:57.533 --> 00:01:03.133
If you want to use a specific Galaxy AI feature, tap the feature name to configure its settings.

13
00:01:03.133 --> 00:01:08.373
In our example, we’ll configure the Interpreter app by downloading additional language packs

14
00:01:08.373 --> 00:01:10.832
and enabling the Tap to talk option.

15
00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:14.226
When you launch the Galaxy AI app for the first time, 

16
00:01:14.226 --> 00:01:19.366
you may also be required to enable certain app permissions before the app can be used. 

17
00:01:20.233 --> 00:01:28.099
Let’s take a close look at one of the most powerful Galaxy AI features that can be used for business purposes: the Interpreter app. 

18
00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:32.333
The Interpreter app can significantly enhance business productivity 

19
00:01:32.333 --> 00:01:36.333
by facilitating seamless communication in multilingual environments.

20
00:01:51.833 --> 00:01:55.551
If you wish to sign out of your Samsung business account on your device, 

21
00:01:55.552 --> 00:02:00.299
you can do so by opening the Settings app, then tapping Accounts and backup.

22
00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:02.766
On the next screen, tap Manage accounts,

23
00:02:03.166 --> 00:02:07.066
Then tap the Samsung account icon, then tap Remove account.

24
00:02:07.300 --> 00:02:12.733
On the Sign out screen, enter your Samsung business account password, then tap OK. 

25
00:02:14.133 --> 00:02:18.511
To learn more about Samsung account for business and the topics covered in this video, 

26
00:02:18.512 --> 00:02:22.133
please see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

27
00:02:22.133 --> 00:02:24.166
Thanks for watching!

